NAME		tell
SYNTAX		tell <user>[,<user>,<user>,.....] <message>
DESCRIPTION	Send a message to a user or list of users.
		a 'user' can be:
			A logged on user's name.
			A user at another host on intermud (ie. user@host)
			A grupe id (ie. #grupe)
		Any members not currently logged on are ignored.

		If <message> begins with a : character, then the message
		is sent as a 'remote'
		If <message> begins with a . character, then the message
		is sent as a 'feeling'

AKA		>
SEE ALSO	grupe, remote, reply
